  "market_context": "EURUSD on the 60-minute chart in a broader downtrend, price retraced higher after forming equal lows near 1.0810 that align with previous day low, creating sell-side liquidity resting below. Price moved from internal liquidity back toward an hourly PD array before continuing lower.",
  "key_observation": "A bearish breaker block formed from a high-low-higher high-lower low sequence overlaps with a bearish fair value gap on the hourly chart, creating a unicorn model directly above equal lows / previous day low that serve as the draw on liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified previous day low and equal lows around 1.0810 as resting sell-side liquidity and the draw on liquidity.",
    "Noted price ran a swing high during the retracement, forming a high-low-higher high-lower low structure.",
    "Marked the series of down-close candles as the bearish breaker block.",
    "Observed a bearish fair value gap overlapping the breaker block, confirming the unicorn model confluence.",
    "Set entry at the breaker block / FVG zone with stop above the swing high.",
    "Targeted the equal lows / previous day low as sell-side liquidity below."
  ],
  "outcome": "Entry filled at the unicorn zone and price reached take profit at the equal lows.",
  "lessons": "When a breaker block overlaps with a fair value gap on the hourly, the unicorn model can be executed directly on the hourly timeframe without dropping lower, provided a clear liquidity target like equal lows or PDL is present.",
